3.1  The study region}
\par \pard\plain \s0\qj\widctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\dbch\af8\dbch\af9\afs24\cf0\kerning1\langfe2052\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\sl240\slmult1\qj\widctlpar\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb60\sa0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
Tanzania was chosen as the study region because of its location in sub-Saharan Africa, the probable effects of climate change in the region and rice is planted widely across the country (Table 1) [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Rowhani2011 \\h }{\fldrslt Rowhani2011}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
]. The bulk of the rice crop is grown from December until June of the following year during the rainy season. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\qj\widctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\dbch\af8\dbch\af9\afs24\cf0\kerning1\langfe2052\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\sl240\slmult1\qj\widctlpar\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi360{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
According to the International Panel on Climate Change (IPCC), East Africa and especially the Great Lakes Region are among the more vulnerable regions in Africa to climate change, where the trend is towards increasing temperatures and declining rainfall according to General Circulation Model outputs [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Boko2007 \\h }{\fldrslt Boko2007}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
]. Temperatures are predicted to increase 2C by 2050, which in turn are predicted to negatively affect rice yields [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Rowhani2011 \\h }{\fldrslt Rowhani2011}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
].}
