3.2.3  Model coupling}
\par \pard\plain \s0\qj\widctlpar\ltrpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\dbch\af8\dbch\af9\afs24\cf0\kerning1\langfe2052\alang1081\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\sl240\slmult1\qj\widctlpar\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb60\sa0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
To facilitate coupling of EPIRICE to RICEPEST, a temporal disaggregation function was incorporated into the EPIRICE model. With this function, the modified EPIRICE model produced daily, spatially representative and non-cumulative percentage disease severity data as outputs instead of the single cumulated output, AUDPC. The time-series of daily percentage disease severity data for BB and LB produced by the modified EPIRICE model were then used as inputs for RICEPEST. Both models were linked to a geographic information system (GIS). EPIRICE is implemented in the R language using the following packages: cropsim [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Hijmans2009 \\h }{\fldrslt Hijmans2009}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
], oldweather [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Hijmans2009 \\h }{\fldrslt Hijmans2009}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
], raster [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Hijmans2014 \\h }{\fldrslt Hijmans2014}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
], rgdal [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Bivand2014 \\h }{\fldrslt Bivand2014}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
], and RODBC [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_Ripley2013 \\h }{\fldrslt Ripley2013}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
], while this version of RICEPEST is implemented in Python language [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_python \\h }{\fldrslt python}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
], using the ArcPy package, as a script in the ArcGIS platform [}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BIB_ESRI2011 \\h }{\fldrslt ESRI2011}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
]. A loose coupling approach was adopted due to the different implementation environments. This approach provided flexibility in data handling and data interoperability (Figure }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
{\field{\*\fldinst  REF BMFlowchart \\h }{\fldrslt ?}}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24
).}
